TEDxLagos brought together Africans from different walks of life to Muson Centre, Onikan on Saturday, August 18, 2018 for a day of deep insights, talks, networking and so much more.  The event which was themed ‘Spotlight’ and anchored by Ace Comedian, Bovi and Founder, Bellanaija, Uche Pedro featured 12 speakers and 2 performers ranging from a Historian, to a Cultural Entrepreneur, Disability Advocates, Media Personality, Health Advocate amongst others.  Speakers included Olasupo Shasore, Clare Omatseye, and Tokini Peterside while there were performances by guitarist Femi Leye and the Dreamcatchers Dance Academy. It was indeed a day filled with inspiration and passion.  A standing ovation greeted Tope Okupe who spoke on building structures with disabled people in mind. James George shared futuristic plans that could help transform the architectural landscape in Nigeria and Olubankole Wellington emphasized the need for us to take action and fix the Nation.  The foyer of the Agip Hall at Muson Centre was transformed into an exhibition area/simulcast lounge and this served as a means of engaging the audience alongside the outdoor activity areas and workshops organized by Skoll Foundation and Union Bank. The event was brought to a close with a Networking Cocktail by Johnnie Walker.  TEDxLagos was brought to you in partnership with Union Bank, Skoll Foundation, Bellanaija, DottsMediaHouse, Penzaarville, Businessday, Cinematics, Vanguard, and Guardian. Photos and Videos from the event will be up soon. Please follow @tedxlagosng on Facebook, Twitter and Instagram to keep up with all happenings.   